Colouration. Larger female holotype (
Fig. 8
) freshly dead, generally translucent, body and appendages covered with larger red and scattered small black spots. Lack of reddish colouration in detached second pereiopod may be due to having become separated. Smaller female paratype (
Fig. 9
) generally a deep uniform orange colouration, without transparent spots.
